#Text=Brazilian surfer wins world championship in Pichilemu , Chile
#Text=Monday , May 30 , 2011
#Text=Promotional poster of the world championship .
#Text=Image : Quiksilver .
#Text=Attendants to the Quiksilver ceremonial , looking forwards to the Punta de Lobos rocks .
#Text=Image : Diego Grez .
#Text=The fourteenth Quiksilver Ceremonial Punta de Lobos Big Wave Invitational surf championship took place on Saturday in the Chilean city of Pichilemu , often called the " Capital of the Surf . "

#Text=In this year 's competition , 24 surfers from countries such as South Africa , Peru , Chile , the United States , and Argentina participated in the championship , including Pichileminians Ramón Navarro and Cristian Merelló , and Hawaiian Köhl Christensen .
#Text=The surfers competed for a US$ 20,000 prize .
#Text=Background
#Text=The Quiksilver Ceremonial Punta de Lobos has been a tradition since 1998 .
#Text=Christensen won that championship , and has regularly participated in it since then , according to La Tercera .
#Text=" If [ the Chilean waves ] were n't that good , I would n't come back .

#Text= There was great expectation in Punta de Lobos yesterday [ on Friday ] , " La Tercera reported .

column1: #Text=" It has arrived the same amount of people coming a long holiday weekend to Pichilemu , but this time , only to see the championship , " director of surf magazine Glass . cl Rodrigo Farías told the newspaper .
#Text=Farías also told La Tercera that during last year 's ceremonial there were waves eight-meters high , and " [ Saturday] 's waves are expected to be more ordained . "
#Text=He predicted that it would be " a bit cloudy , and there will be more time between one wave and another , so there could be more tubes , which will be much better visually . "
#Text=The championship
#Text=Video footage of the first stage of the semi finals of the Quiksilver Ceremonial Punta de Lobos .
#Text=Image : Diego Grez .
#Text=The surfers dropped into the sea to begin the championship at 07:30 local time ( 11:30 UTC ) .
#Text=It is estimated that least two thousand people from Chile and other countries attended the event throughout the day .
#Text=A helicopter flew overhead at Punta de Lobos , recording and photographing the surfers and attendants .
#Text=The attendants were given free fruit juice , fruits , as well as Red Bull drinks at the end of the day .

#Text=The 24 competing surfers were : Köhl Christensen , Carlos Burle , Marcos Monteiro , Peter Mel , Chris Bertish , Ramón Navarro , Diego Medina , Cristian Merello , Rusty Long , Grant " Twiggy " Baker , Fernando Zegers , Reinaldo Ibarra , Greg Long , Gabriel Villarán , Jamie Sterling , Anthony Taschnick , Mark Healey , Kealii Mamala , Jaimie Mitchell , Danilo Couto , Sebastian de Romana , León Vicuña , and Matías López .
#Text=The Quiksilver Ceremonial Punta de Lobos was broadcasted live in HD quality for the first time in the championship 's history through its official website .
#Text=The footage included underwater shots .
#Text=The championship lasted until 17:30 local time ( 21:30 UTC ) , and the results were as follows :
